            Having said that, may I go on to draw the attention of the Committee to Clause 8(1):
            <q>The Commission may issue a determination in respect of a proposed public procession imposing on the persons organising or taking part in it such conditions as the Commission considers necessary".</q>
            As I read that, it could cover such matters as the dates of parades referred to by the noble Lord, Lord Fitt. Then in lines 44 to 45, it goes on:
            <q>may include conditions as to the route of the procession",</q>
